.TH "platform_get_irq" 9 "platform_get_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_get_irq \- get an IRQ for a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" platform_get_irq
.BI "(struct platform_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
platform device
.IP "num" 12
IRQ number index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets an IRQ for a platform device and prints an error message if finding the
IRQ fails. Device drivers should check the return value for errors so as to
not pass a negative integer value to the \fBrequest_irq\fP APIs.

For example::

int irq = platform_get_irq(pdev, 0);
if (irq < 0)
return irq;
.SH "RETURN"
non-zero IRQ number on success, negative error number on failure.
